Class RoutineTest

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    junit.framework.Test

    public class RoutineTest
extends BaseJDBCTestCase
    Set of tests for SQL routines. This tests mainly the SQL definition of routines and the server-side behaviour of routines. Calling of procedures is tested in ProcedureTest.

      • testFunctionNullHandling

        public void testFunctionNullHandling()
                              throws java.sql.SQLException,
                                     java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException
        Test that functions handle being called or not called when it is passed a NULL argument correctly. A function can be declared: RETURNS NULL ON NULL INPUT - any argument being NULL means the function is returns NULL without being called. CALLED ON NULL INPUT (default) - function is always called regardless of any arguement being NULL.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException
        java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException
